  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of oil in a large skillet or wok over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the sliced pork and cook until browned, about 3-4 minutes. Remove from the skillet and set aside.",
    "Add the remaining 1 tablespoon of oil to the skillet and add the sliced chilies, minced garlic, and mixed bell peppers.",
    "Cook until the vegetables are tender, about 3-4 minutes.",
    "Add the cooked pork back into the skillet and stir in the soy sauce, fish sauce (if using), brown sugar, and rice vinegar.",
    "Cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, until the sauce has thickened.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Serve hot over steamed rice.",
